node.title: Likely new Omicron case found in NSW, hundreds of COVID-19 swabs to be retested
node.alt: Brad Hazzard the health minister looks concerned
node.description: NSW Health Minister Brad Hazzard says a sixth case of the Omicron COVID-19 variant has likely been discovered in the state.
node.content:
["NSW Health Minister Brad Hazzard says a sixth case of the Omicron COVID-19 variant has been discovered in the state.", "The man in his 40s is isolating in Sydney's west, and arrived on a flight from Doha last Thursday.", "NSW Health has asked all those on the flight to come forward for testing.", "Genomic sequencing is underway to determine if the man has the Omicron variant, but Mr Hazzard said early testing showed it was likely he had the new strain.", "\"He came to Sydney on the same flight as a number of other cases\", he said.", "\"We believe it is likely that it\u00a0will be\u00a0confirmed later this afternoon as a definite\u00a0Omicron case.\"", "He has been active in the community.", "NSW Health is retesting COVID-19 swabs collected over the past two weeks from anyone who has been in southern Africa, where the variant was first identified,\u00a0to see if more infections can be identified.", "\"There was no awareness of Omicron until last Thursday or Friday, it seems like a lifetime ago already, but it was only a few days ago,\" Mr Hazzard said.", "Mr Hazzard said about 300 of those had been double-checked so far.", "Health authorities yesterday confirmed a traveller from southern Africa, and the fifth NSW confirmed case of the latest variant, had spent at least two days in the community while\u00a0infectious.", "A woman in her 30s who landed\u00a0in Sydney on Thursday, before new travel restrictions were in place, had visited at least two southern African countries before arriving in Australia.", "Contact tracing determined the fully-vaccinated woman visited several retails stores in Sydney's west and fast food outlets in the Central Coast.", "More to come.", "", "
Heavily mutated Omicron variant puts scientist on alert
"]
